    <stitle>DCM AND DDM DRUM TYPE PARKING BRAKE - BENDIX DUO DUTY MECHANICAL BRAKE - REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0402114">Figure 14</hotlnk>for all Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0402114" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g0402114" filename="../figg04/g0402114.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. DDM Brake Exploded View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BRAKE SHOE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SUPPORT PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. UPPER ANCHOR PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOWER ANCHOR PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SHOE RETURN SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. SHOE GUIDE LUG</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. SHOE BEARING SURFACES</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. SHOE TO SHOE SPRING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Brake Shoe Reassembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the ends of the shoe-to-shoe spring (Item 8) into lower holes of the brake
                    shoes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Spread open upper (applying) ends of the shoes and assemble lower ends of the shoes over
                    shoulder of lower anchor pin (Item 4) with a twisting motion of the shoes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move upper ends of the shoes to the upper anchor pin (Item 3), inserting the shoe webs
                    between guide lugs (Item 6) and bearing surfaces (Item 7) of the support plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With upper ends of the shoes against the upper anchor pin (Item 3), install the two
                    return springs (Item 5) using a spring installing tool. Install short hooks of springs into upper
                    holes of the brake shoes and hook opposite ends of the springs over the anchor pin nib. Springs must
                    be installed over anchor pin nib with open end of hooks toward center line of brake to provide
                    proper clearance for camshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
